.TH "cik_sdma_emit_copy_buffer" 9 "cik_sdma_emit_copy_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cik_sdma_emit_copy_buffer \- copy buffer using the sDMA engine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cik_sdma_emit_copy_buffer
.BI "(struct amdgpu_ib *ib "  ","
.BI "uint64_t src_offset "  ","
.BI "uint64_t dst_offset "  ","
.BI "uint32_t byte_count "  ","
.BI "bool tmz "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ib" 12
indirect buffer to copy to
.IP "src_offset" 12
src GPU address
.IP "dst_offset" 12
dst GPU address
.IP "byte_count" 12
number of bytes to xfer
.IP "tmz" 12
is this a secure operation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Copy GPU buffers using the DMA engine (CIK).
Used by the amdgpu ttm implementation to move pages if
registered as the asic copy callback.
